Date: Fri, 29 Sep 2000 11:32:02 GMT
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source:Canadian News Network, Fri 29 Sep 2000 11:32:02 GMT [edited
<http://www.newswire.ca/releases/September2000/29/c8310.html>

Canadian Company Contracted to Spray Mosquitos, Eliminate Health Risk
---------------------------------------------------------------------
TORONTO: Skylink Aviation Inc., a Canadian rapid response air logistics
company specializing in peacekeeping, emergency and disaster relief
missions, has been contracted to send helicopters and aircraft to Saudi
Arabia to spray mosquitos that have caused an outbreak of Rift Valley fever.
Skylink's fleet of 7 helicopters and 11 fixed wing aircraft was on the
ground in Saudi Arabia yesterday and will begin spraying mosquitos today (29
Sep 2000) throughout Jizan, a low altitude area in the southwestern part of
Saudi Arabia bordering on Yemen to the south and the Red Sea to the west.
Skylink, which has a US$1.7 million contract for spraying with the Kingdom
of Saudi Arabia, has 2 managers now in Saudi Arabia, to manage the
logistics of the spraying operation that will continue for 3 months and
provide for 3000 hours of spraying.
